Permanent delegates to the National Council of Provinces (NCOP) will this week visit their respective provinces for the Provincial Week Programme to assess delivery of services to citizens. Held under the theme “Assessing State capacity to respond to the needs of communities”, the Provincial Week to start from 29 March to 01 April 2022 is a high-impact oversight programme aimed at responding to the challenges of state capacity in the provinces. It is further intended to afford permanent delegates to the NCOP with an opportunity to return to their provinces to assess service delivery. Parliamentary spokesperson, Moloto Mothapo, said the NCOP delegates, together with their provincial legislature counterparts, will spend the week interacting with municipalities on interventions to improve governance challenges and the state of service delivery. “This Provincial Week 2022 will allow each provincial delegations to concentrate on matters that affect the province in the national sphere of government,” Mothapo said in a statement. The provincial focus areas aimed at addressing issues affecting each of the nine provinces including: